Visualize few images¶

In [58]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def generate_list_of_images(file_path):
    
    imgs, labels = [], []
    with open(file_path) as f:
        lines = f.readlines()
        
        for line in lines:
            line = line.split()
            imgs.append(line[0].split(",")[0])
            labels.append(line[1].split(",")[0])
            
    return imgs, labels

def visualize(image, mask):
    fontsize = 18

    f, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(8, 8))

    ax[0].imshow(image)
    ax[1].imshow(mask)
In [59]:
imgs, labels = generate_list_of_images(root_dir + "train.csv")
In [61]:
# randomly select 10 images
import random

pairs = list(zip(imgs, labels))
random_select = random.sample(pairs, 10)

for pair in random_select:
    img = cv2.imread(pair[0])
    img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2. COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    mask = cv2.imread(pair[1], -1)
    
    visualize(img, mask)
